In order to ensure the safety of the wireless charging function, you must read and fully understand the following precautions and only use the function according to the prompts：
 1. Only the equipment compatible with the wireless charging standard of Qi can be charged. The charging equipment must be placed the center position in the charging tank, i.e. within the charging range, to avoid intermittent charging and reduced charging efficiency; 
 2. In order to avoid disturbing the start of the vehicle, the wireless charging function will be interrupted during the process of vehicle key certification, and the wireless charging function can be restored after the completion of vehicle key certification; 
 3. Do not put or leave objects between the charging board and the charging equipment; Pay special attention to coins, keys, rings, ornaments, bus cards, silver cards and other similar items; 
 4. If the equipment or metal foreign matters incompatible with the wireless charging standard of Qi are placed in the charging area, the charging may be interrupted, the object may become hot, and the charging board may be damaged when the object enters. After the object cools down, remove it.

Suggestions on electric tailgate hight adjustment：
 for users with a height of less than 1.6 meters, it is recommended to open 80% of the height; 
 For users 1.6-1.7 meters tall, the recommended opening height is 90%; 
 For users with a height of more than 1.7 meters, 100% height is recommended.
 Relevant height adjustment suggestions are for reference only
